<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-07-01" class=3D"date-past">01 Jul 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The following fie=
lds are out-of-scope for the first version&nbsp;</p><p><br></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span>ABN or tax exemption provided?</span></li>
<li><s><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Credit Interest redirected?</s=
pan></s></li>
<li><p><span>Gross credit interest</span></p></li>
<li><p><s><span>Debit interest</span></s></p></li>
<li><p><s><span>Debit interest rate</span></s></p></li>
<li><p><s><span>Credit interest rate</span></s></p></li>
<li><p><s><span>Interest rate type</span></s></p></li>
<li><p><s><span>Interest rate structure</span></s></p></li>
</ul><p><br></p><p><br></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Agreed</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M058573" =
href=3D"/display/~M058573" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1125291984" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Ave Cahyadi</a> <a class=3D"c=
onfluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M061387" href=3D"/display=
/~M061387" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1359044573" data-linked-resource-vers=
ion=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://c=
onfluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Thomas Van Deun</a> <a class=3D"confluence-us=
erlink user-mention" data-username=3D"F079288" href=3D"/display/~F079288" d=
ata-linked-resource-id=3D"1415102363" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" da=
ta-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.sr=
v.westpac.com.au">Melinda Jamieson</a></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">These fields need mo=
re business requirements</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">2</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-07-02" class=3D"date-past">02 Jul 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Usage of the fiel=
ds:</p>
<ul>
<li><span><span>ABN or tax exemption provided?&nbsp;</span></span><p><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(163,21,21);">=E2=86=92 taxResidencyApplied has a differ=
ent meaning than the requirement:&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"margin-left: =
0.0px;">This attribute is only applicable for Australian Customers. The att=
ribute determines whether a Customer has selected to apply their primary ta=
x residence status to a Subscription 'true' or to opt out of this 'false'. =
This selection will impact WHT calculation if configured.</p></li>
</ul><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>This field requires elaboration and is dependant on solutioning of <span=
 class=3D"jira-issue" data-jira-key=3D"ART-958"> <a href=3D"https://jira.sr=
v.westpac.com.au/browse/ART-958" class=3D"jira-issue-key"><img class=3D"ico=
n" src=3D"https://jira.srv.westpac.com.au:8444/secure/viewavatar?size=3Dxsm=
all&amp;avatarId=3D10300&amp;avatarType=3Dissuetype">ART-958</a> - <span cl=
ass=3D"summary">Business Account Withholding Tax Phase 2 (GCM Integration)<=
/span> <span class=3D"aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle             aui-lozeng=
e-default
     jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">In Review</span> </span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M061387" =
href=3D"/display/~M061387" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1359044573" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Thomas Van Deun</a>&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">This field is OOS. <=
span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">This is a back log item in the Unite p=
rogram, but is not yet scheduled.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">3</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The field:</p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Credit Interest redirected?</span=
></li>
</ul><p>=E2=86=92 We can use the functionality <a class=3D"external-link" h=
ref=3D"https://docs.10xbanking.com/b2b/reference/createsubscriptionlinks" r=
el=3D"nofollow">https://docs.10xbanking.com/b2b/reference/createsubscriptio=
nlinks</a> and <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://docs.10xbanking.c=
om/b2b/reference/searchsubscriptionlinks" rel=3D"nofollow">https://docs.10x=
banking.com/b2b/reference/searchsubscriptionlinks</a> to determine if a lin=
k has been established.</p><p><br></p><p>This returns an internal subscript=
ionKey. Before we return the response to the UI, we will look up the intern=
al subKey in 10x and resolve it to accountnumber and BSB&nbsp;</p><p><br></=
p><p><br></p><p><strong>-- Currently there is no journey to establish this =
redirect - so is it worth doing this now?</strong></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">TBD later</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">4</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-07-01" class=3D"date-past">01 Jul 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The fields relate=
d to interest summary:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><p><span>Gross credit interest</span></p></li>
<li><p><span>Debit interest</span></p></li>
</ul><p><span>need to be part of it's own feature. The impact of surfacing =
these fields require ACD input for new resources on downstream APIS.</span>=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">TBD later</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">5</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-06-24" class=3D"date-past">24 Jun 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The field:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span>Date opened</span></li>
<li><p><span>Date closed</span></p></li>
</ul><p><span>Will be returned in the standard response of the POST /arrang=
ements call</span></p><p><br></p><p><span>GCM will be the source for both f=
ields</span></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The account host =
(10x) does not have a dedicated field for account closure date.</p><p><br><=
/p><p>GCM does record this, hence it's the preferred system to source it fr=
om</p><p><br></p><p>Account opening date is available both on GCM and 10x, =
but 10x records the technical opening date which could be different than th=
e actual opening date for customer (which GCM can have)</p><p><br></p><p>KD=
: Use GCM for both fields</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M061387" =
href=3D"/display/~M061387" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1359044573" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Thomas Van Deun</a>&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">6</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-06-24" class=3D"date-past">24 Jun 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The field</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><p><span>Last transaction date</span></p></li>
</ul><p><span>will be derived from the existing POST /transactions endpoint=
 and use the first object in the response to determine the date</span></p><=
/td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">UI component to make=
 call and gets 'newest' transaction date, specified using pageSize=3D1 and =
pageKey=3D0</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M061387" =
href=3D"/display/~M061387" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1359044573" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Thomas Van Deun</a>&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">7</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-06-24" class=3D"date-past">24 Jun 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The fields:</p>
<ul>
<li><p><span>Debit interest rate</span></p></li>
<li><p><span>Credit interest rate</span></p></li>
<li><p><span>Interest rate type</span></p></li>
<li><p><span>Interest rate structure</span></p></li>
</ul><p><br></p><p><span>Will be returned in an optional object in POST /ar=
rangements call. The caller can specify this by adding this the to 'fields'=
 query parameter in the EXP api.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span>In 10x, we a=
re investigating the use of <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://docs=
.10xbanking.com/b2b/reference/calculateinterestsrates" rel=3D"nofollow">htt=
ps://docs.10xbanking.com/b2b/reference/calculateinterestsrates</a> for this=
 purpose</span></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">TBD later</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><br></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
