<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><p><span><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"4e287d19-9f2=
c-4bed-92de-583dce455594">Gross credit interest</span></span></p></li>
<li><p><span>Debit interest</span></p></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Currently we cannot filter on specific type of t=
ransaction code. We cannot aggregate transactions in the API. 10x is capabl=
e of tallying up the total amount for x transactions</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>XP APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>Change to existing TXN Listing endpoint support 'filter' and 'aggregate=
' parameters (including API Specs and DTD)</li>
</ul><p>W1C APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>Change to existing TXN Listing endpoint support 'filter' and 'aggregate=
'&nbsp; parameters (including API Specs and DTD)</li>
</ul><p>10x APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>Change to existing TXN Listing endpoint support 'filter' and 'aggregate=
'&nbsp; parameters (including API Specs and DTD)</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>L</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Credit Interest redirected?</span=
></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Currently not returned by any W1C API.&nbsp;<=
/p><p>Endpoints exists in 10x&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>EXP APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>New or Change to existing endpoint get account redirects (including API=
 Specs and DTD)</li>
<li>Implementation of entitlement masking on linked account</li>
</ul><p>W1C APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>New or Change to existing endpoint to get account redirects (including =
API Specs and DTD)</li>
</ul><p>10x APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>New INF API (1) with new endpoint to get account redirects (including A=
PI Specs and DTD)</li>
<li>New callout to 10x endpoint to check if subscription has redirect</li>
<li>New callout to 10x endpoint to resolve 'internal subscriptionKey' to ac=
c + bsb</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>XL</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false">7</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>Interest cycle (monthly)</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Currently not returned by any W1C API.&nbsp;<=
/p><p>Endpoints exists in 10x&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>EXP APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>New or Change to existing endpoint get account product level details (i=
ncluding API Specs and DTD)</li>
</ul><p>W1C APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>New or Change to existing endpoint to get account details (including AP=
I Specs and DTD)</li>
</ul><p>10x APIs</p>
<ul>
<li>New INF API (2) with new endpoint to get account details (including API=
 Specs and DTD)</li>
<li>New callout to 10x endpoint to fetch these rates</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>XL</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"id-04.SD:Accountsnapshot,accountdetailsandviewingclosedaccounts(C=
ustomerPortal)-Solution"><span>Solution</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"id-04.SD:Accountsnapshot,accountdetailsandviewingclosedaccounts(C=
ustomerPortal)-SolutionOverview"><span>Solution Overview</span></h2>
<p><span><a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D1742161648">Account Sna=
pshot &amp; Details UI Mapping [ERM 25E2 - February 2025]</a></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Component</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Change</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Outcome</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">API Spec changes&nbsp;</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Westpac One C=
ore Arrangement CAP API</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span class=3D"toc-item-body"><a class=3D"toc=
-link" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/cap-prods=
vcadm-proddealacctadm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1#capprodsvcadmproddealacctadmin=
stlarrngmntsvcngv1-POST/arrangements/summaryView" rel=3D"nofollow">POST /ar=
rangements/summaryView</a></span></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>include startDateTime and endDateTime from GCM account lookup in respon=
se</li>
<li>optional query parameter to GCM to fetch ACTIVE or INACTIVE &amp; ACTIV=
E accounts</li>
</ul><p><br></p><p><strong>NEW </strong><span class=3D"toc-item-body"><a cl=
ass=3D"toc-link" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC=
/cap-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1#capprodsvcadmproddea=
lacctadminstlarrngmntsvcngv1-POST/arrangements/detailView" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>POST /arrangements/detailView</a></span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>EXP API can retrieve Open Date and Close date=
 of an accounts</p><p><br></p><p>EXP API can retrieve details information a=
bout 1 account</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbu=
cket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-prodsvcadm-proddealaccta=
dm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1-api/browse?at=3Drefs%2Fheads%2Fswagger-review-feb=
25" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repo=
s/wdp-cap-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1-api/browse?at=
=3Drefs%2Fheads%2Fswagger-review-feb25</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan=3D"3" class=3D"confluenceTd">Galaxy Accounts MFE</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>EXP API - GET Arrangements</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>New mapping to include openedDateTime and closedDateTime in response sc=
hema</li>
<li>optional query parameter to W1C CAP to fetch ACTIVE or INACTIVE &amp; A=
CTIVE accounts</li>
</ul><p>EXP API - <strong>New </strong>endpoint POST /arrangementDetail</p>=
<p><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/exp-galaxy-account-v2#expgalaxyaccountv2-Capabi=
lity:GetDetailsofanArrangement(Feb25)">exp-galaxy-account-v2#Capability:Get=
DetailsofanArrangement(Feb25)</a></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbu=
cket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-account-microfrontend/bro=
wse?at=3Drefs%2Fheads%2Fswagger-review-feb25" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitb=
ucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-account-microfrontend/br=
owse?at=3Drefs%2Fheads%2Fswagger-review-feb25</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>New UI Component that</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>POST Arrangements with accountnumber and bsb of selected account</li>
<li>POST Transactions Listing with account number and bsb, pageSize =3D1 pa=
geKey =3D0</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">We can show the snapshot of the account with las=
t transaction on information</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>New UI Tab 'Account Details'</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>POST Arrangements with accountnumber and bsb of selected account</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">In the account details tab UI&nbsp; we can show =
dates&nbsp; Open Date and Close date of an account</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Galaxy Payments MFE</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>EXP API:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>New mapping to include openedDateTime and closedDateTime in response sc=
hema</li>
<li>optional query parameter to W1C CAP to fetch ACTIVE or INACTIVE &amp; A=
CTIVE accounts</li>
</ul><p><br></p><p>For dropdown's that only need to show active accounts:</=
p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li style=3D"list-style-type: none;">
<ol>
<li>Use INACTIVE &amp; ACTIVE query param to fetch arrangements</li>
<li>Then in the EXP API, filter all out all accounts that have STATUS =3D C=
LOSED</li>
<li>Return the updated array to the UI</li>
</ol></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbu=
cket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-payment-microfrontend/bro=
wse?at=3Drefs%2Fheads%2Fswagger-review-feb25" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitb=
ucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-payment-microfrontend/br=
owse?at=3Drefs%2Fheads%2Fswagger-review-feb25</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Wash API</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>NEW API - POST /accounts/detailView</p><p><a =
href=3D"/display/BANKPT/cap-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-10xacctsvcng-v1#capp=
rodsvcadmproddealacctadm10xacctsvcngv1-Capability:Retrievethedetailsofanacc=
ount">cap-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-10xacctsvcng-v1#Capability:Retrievethe=
detailsofanaccount</a></p><p><br></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-04.SD:Accountsnapshot,accountdetailsandviewingclosedaccounts(C=
ustomerPortal)-Showinginactiveaccounts:">Showing inactive accounts:</h3>
<p>W1C will keep consuming <span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">GCM <span>=
&nbsp;</span></span><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://mesh.westpac=
.com.au/components/apis/inf-bnkng-arrngmnt-arrngmntpartyrole-arrngmntcust-v=
2" rel=3D"nofollow">POST /arrangementSearch endpoin</a> to retrieve arrange=
ment details. The uplift will be to include optional header parameter: <spa=
n style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp;arrangementStatus<span> </span>to t=
his endpoint which allows the consumer to provide ACTIVE, ACTIVE_AND_INACTI=
VE.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">The EXP API's that implement these=
 GET or POST arrangements on will be able to pass on the optional query par=
ameter to indicate which accounts to retrieve. It will be flexible, allowin=
g the UI component to decide what to call.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">The following parameter is applica=
ble on both W1C Cap API and EXP API's&nbsp;</span></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Parameter location</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">name</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">type</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">allowed values</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Query</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">arrangemen=
tStatus</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">string</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>ACTIVE , ACTIVE_AND_INACTIVE</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">Account st=
atus. "ACTIVE" will fetch arrangements which are active only. "ACTIVE_AND_I=
NACTIVE " will fetch arrangements which are Active and Inactive both. If us=
er is not passing this query parameter then default option of ACTIVE_AND_IN=
ACTIVE will be used.</span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>Retention period:</p>
<p>In GCM, accounts will remain 7 years after a customer has been closed.&n=
bsp;</p>
<p><span><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/Inactive+Accounts+Analysis">Inactive Acco=
unts Analysis</a></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-04.SD:Accountsnapshot,accountdetailsandviewingclosedaccounts(C=
ustomerPortal)-SequenceDiagram"><span>Sequence Diagram</span></h2>
<p>2 API calls need to be executed from the account MFE to show the account=
 details/snapshot view</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>POST /arrangementDetail</li>
<li>POST /transactionListing with explicit paging parameters: <span style=
=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">pageSize=3D1</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>POST /arrangementDetail</strong></p>
<p><map id=3D"gliffy-map-1793426973-9170" name=3D"gliffy-map-1793426973-917=
0"></map></p>
<table width=3D"100%" class=3D"gliffy-macro-table">
